Description: A pottery sherd of Egyptian marl clay with scratched marks on the exterior surface. The marks were incised post-production.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 27
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 27 has been scratched into interior surface.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.115, p.129, p.209, p.224, pl.66)
